    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "SEPTEMBER 1994\n$2.50\nA.B. Hirschfeld Press\n5200 Smith Road\nDenver, CO 80216\nSTAPLETON\nInternational Airport",
      "THE DIFFERENCE\nFINE DINING AND EXECUTIVE MEAL OPTION\nPREMIUM FRENCH WINES AND CHAMPAGNE\nDIGITAL ELECTRONIC CONTROL UNIT\nSTATE-O TEEPER SELECTRONIC\nADJUSTABLE ELECTRONIC LUMBAR SUPPORT -\nADJUSTABLE ELECTRONIC FOOTREST\nBUSINESSi\nRS T\nINTRODUCING BUSINESSFIRST.sM\nFIRST CLASS COMFORT. BUSINESS CLASS FARE\nYou want First Class. So why settle for regular Business\nClass on international flights? That's why Continental\ncreated BusinessFirst SM -the comfort and service of\nInternational First Class at a Business Class fare.\nWe started with a new custom-crafted electronic sleeper\nseat-the only true Business Class sleeper seat of any major\nairline. Our 55\" seat pitch provides more room than the\nusual 40\"-42\" offered by other major airlines. And our new\nBusinessFirst cabin features a spacious two-abreast\nseating configuration so you'll never have more than one\nneighbor sitting next to you.\nCall your travel agent or Continental at 1-800-231-0856\nfor more information.\nAnd discover an\nInternational Business\nClass that's\nContinental\nOne Airline Can Make A Difference.\"\nFirst Class.\n© 1993 Continental Airlines, Inc."
    ],
